		<title>Formulas</title>

		<p>
			Formulas are used for many purposes, including finding constants or solving specific types of equations. Various disciplines, such as finance, have specific formulas to evaluate quantitiies.
		</p>


		<subsection xml:id="formulas-used-to-find-constants" class="unnumbered">
			<title>Formulas used to find constants:</title>

			<p>
				<alert>Rate of Change/Slope (of Linear) Formula:<alert> <me>\displaystyle \text{rate of change = }\frac{\text{1st dep - 2nd dep}}{\text{1st indep - 2nd indep}}</me>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Intercept (of Linear) Formula:<alert><me>\text{intercept} = \text{dep} -  \text{slope} \ast \text{indep}</me>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Percent Change Formula:<alert>
			</p>

			<p><ul>
				<li>
							<p>
				If a quantity changes by a percentage corresponding to growth rate <m>r</m>, then the growth factor is <me>\displaystyle g=1+r</me>
			</p>
				</li>

				<li>
							<p>
				If the growth factor is <m>g</m>, then the growth rate is <me>r = g-1</me>  
			</p>
				</li>

			</ul></p>

			<p>
				<alert>Growth Factor Formula:<alert>
			</p>

			<p>
				If a quantity is growing (decaying) exponentially, then the growth (decay) factor is <me>\displaystyle g = \sqrt[t]{\frac{a}{s}}</me> where <m>s</m> is the starting amount and <m>a</m> is the amount after <m>t</m> time periods.
			</p>

			<p>
				 
			</p>

		</subsection>

		<subsection xml:id="formulas-used-to-find-solve-specific-types-of-equations" class="unnumbered">
			<title>Formulas used to find solve specific types of equations:</title>

			<p>
				<alert>Root Formula:<alert> The equation <m>C^n=v</m> has solution <m>C= \sqrt[n]{v}</m>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Log-Divides Formula:<alert> The equation <m>g^Y = v</m> has solution <m>\displaystyle Y = \frac{\log (v)}{\log(g)}</m>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Quadratic Formula:<alert> The equation <m>aT^2+bT+c=0</m> has solutions<!-- linebreak --><me>T = \frac{-b}{2a} \pm \frac{\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}</me>
			</p>

		</subsection>

		<subsection xml:id="formulas-from-finance" class="unnumbered">
			<title>Formulas from finance:</title>

			<p>
				<alert>Compound Interest Formula:<alert> <m>\displaystyle a = p \left( 1 + \frac{r}{12}\right) ^{12y}</m>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Equivalent APR Formula:<alert> <m>\displaystyle \text{APR} = \left(1+\frac{r}{12}\right)^{12}-1</m>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Future Value Annuity Formula:<alert> <m>\displaystyle a = p \ast \frac{\left( 1 + \frac{r}{12}\right) ^{12y}-1}{\frac{r}{12}}</m>
			</p>

			<p>
				<alert>Loan Payment Formula:<alert> <m>\displaystyle p = \frac{a  \ast \frac{r}{12}}{1-\left( 1 + \frac{r}{12}\right) ^{-12y}}</m>
			</p>

